Accidental Release Prevention Program and Chemical-Specific Prevention Steps



Prevention of accidental ammonia releases at The Hillshire Brands Company- San Lorenzo is accomplished through sound industry practice in the original ammonia refrigeration system design and construction, the specification and review of system modifications, and the day-to-day operation and maintenance of the system.



-This includes:

AA?    Compliance with industry standards and codes in effect at the time of initial construction and modification;

AA?    Performance of a thorough Process Hazard Analyses (PHAs) at least once every five years using accurate Process Safety Information; 

AA?    Implementation of Operating Procedures.

AA?    Appropriate initial and refresher training of system operations and maintenance personnel;  

AA?    Performance of preventive and corrective maintenance according to system component manufacturer recommendations and pursuant to site wide hazardous energy lockout/tagout and hot work permit programs;

AA?    Application of established auditing, inspection, and pre-start-up review protocols; and

AA?    Use of qualified contractors for work on the system.



